The pandas.DataFrame.select_dtypes() method returns a subset of a DataFrame's columns based on their data types (dtypes). It is useful for quickly isolating columns of a specific type, such as all numeric columns for analysis or all object columns for text processing.
The method uses two primary parameters: include and exclude. At least one parameter must be supplied, but not both with overlapping types.
include: A selection of dtypes or strings to be included.
exclude: A selection of dtypes or strings to be excluded.

