In pandas, the median() function is used to calculate the middle value of data in a Series or DataFrame. It returns the median of values for the requested axis and automatically excludes NA/null values by default.
mode() function gets the mode(s) of each element along the axis selected. Adds a row for each mode per label, fills in gaps with nan.
The .iloc[] property in pandas is used for purely integer-location based indexing. This means you select rows and columns based on their numerical positions, starting from 0, rather than their labels or names.
.name it is a read/write attribute that returns or sets the name of the Series. This name is used for identification, plotting labels, and can become the column name when the Series is converted into a DataFrame.
The pandas.Series.to_frame() method is used to convert a Series object into a single-column DataFrame. This is a common operation when you need the data manipulation capabilities of a DataFrame for data that is currently in a Series format.

